10. Why does this expression cause an error? How can you fix it?
'I have eaten ' + 99 + 'burritos.'

answer:
because 99 in and integer which is numeric data type and 'I have eaten ' and 'burritos.' are string which is text data type
Concatination is possible with different data types

correctin : 'I have eaten ' + str(99) + 'burritos.'
output : 'I have eaten 99 burritos.'       (string : text data type

